label: A3B4C3_cI40_220_a_c_b-001
title: Y$_{3}$Au$_{3}$Sb$_{4}$ Structure
comments: (Lu, 2008) describe this as a \href{current_web_home_dir/A4B3_cI28_220_c_a-001}{filled Th$_{3}$P$_{4}$ ($D7_{3}$) structure}, and, like its parent, there can be considerable disorder on the transition metal site. This is seen in the U$_{3}$NiAs$_{4}$ compound, where 2/3 of the nickel (2b) sites are vacant.
